ite, agissant en son nom et pour son compte, qui cherche un particulier ou un auto-entrepreneur pour réaliser une prestation de service et qui publie dans ce but une ou des annonces d’emploi sur le Site.\n•\tClient : Client qui engage un Prestataire sur la plateforme pour réaliser une prestation de Service\n•\tPrestataire : Particulier ou auto-entrepreneur annonceur inscrit sur le Site, agissant en son nom et pour son compte, qui cherche à être contacté par un Client pour réaliser des prestations de services.\n•\tService : Désigne la prestation de service intermédiée par Mitiim sur son Site ou celui d\'un Partenaire, achetée par le Client suite à son Annonce de d’emploi\n•\tPartenaire : Personne morale qui participe à des négociations avec Mitiim dans le cadre d\'une opération commerciale et représente les mêmes intérêts.\n•\tPlateforme : Interface physique ou digitale permettant au Partenaire de   publier des annonces d’emploi dans le cadre d\'une opération commerciale\n•\tCommande : Annonce d’emploi publiée par les Partenaire ou leurs Clients sur la Plateforme\n•\tPrix forfaitaire : Prix total de la Commande calculé en fonction des besoins du Client\n•\tProfil Prestataire : ensemble des données (texte, photographie, localisation, description de service, coordonnées, …) regroupées dans les annonces d\'offres de services publiées sur le Site par des Prestataires à destination des Clients.\n•\tMembre ou Utilisateur : internaute inscrit sur le Site, qui peut être indépendamment Client ou Prestataire ou les deux.',
      'en':
          'I. GENERAL CONDITIONS\n\n1. Introduction\nMitiim is an advertisement and profile site specializing in the personal service, home service and concierge service sector, operated by Vheos pro Sarl\'s, a simplified limited liability company whose head office is at 5 Abbé edouard Garnich , Alzingen, Luxembourg, under the domain name Mitiim.com which you can use to publish your service announcements as a Customer (service requester) or to reference your service provider profile, called “Service Provider”. Mitiim is available on your internet browser from your computer or any other mobile device via a website or mobile application.\nMitiim offers some content and features for free, but is not completely free. Services only accessible upon payment are clearly detailed and indicated on the site or mobile application. However, fees are not invoiced without explicit warning to the User. Limited use will not be billed to the User. Mitiim is aimed exclusively at individuals or legal entities representing a company, i.e. end consumers, and only they can register on Mitiim.\n\n2. Definitions\n• Mitiim, or the Site: all the functionalities and services provided by the website whose URL is https://Mitiim.com as well as the mobile applications available for the Apple and Android “stores”.\n• Employment: subject of a service request as mentioned in a job advertisement published on the Site or the Application by a Client.\n• Job announcement: all data (text, photography, location, service description, contact details, etc.) grouped in service request announcements published on the Site by individuals for individual or professional Service Providers.\n• Client: individual or professional advertiser registered on the Site, acting in his name and on his behalf, who is looking for an individual or a self-employed person to provide a service and who publishes for this purpose one or more job advertisements on the Site.\n• Client: Client who hires a Service Provider on the platform to provide a Service\n• Service Provider: Individual or self-employed advertiser registered on the Site, acting in his name and on his behalf, who seeks to be contacted by a Client to provide services.\n• Service: Refers to the provision of service intermediated by Mitiim on its Site or that of a Partner, purchased by the Client following their Job Announcement\n• Partner: Legal entity which participates in negotiations with Mitiim within the framework of a commercial transaction and represents the same interests.\n• Platform: Physical or digital interface allowing the Partner to publish job advertisements as part of a commercial operation\n• Order: Job advertisement published by Partners or their Clients on the Platform\n• Fixed price: Total price of the Order calculated according to the Customer\'s needs\n• Service Provider Profile: all data (text, photography, location, service description, contact details, etc.) grouped in service offer announcements published on the Site by Service Providers for Customers.\n• Member or User: Internet user registered on the Site, who can independently be Client or Service Provider or both.',
