iim by email: contact@Mitiim.com.\n5.5 Mitiim reserves the right to refuse the registration of any natural person who does not comply with these General Conditions or the legislation in force.\n\n6. Exclusion and withdrawal of a member\n6.1 Violation of the General Conditions\nAny violation of these General Conditions by a Member may lead to their exclusion from the Site.\n6.2 Other reasons for exclusion\nGenerally speaking, Members undertake to refrain from using the Site for the following purposes:\n• offensive, defamatory, contrary to public order and good morals;\n• infringing on the privacy of third parties;\n• of a directly advertising or promotional nature or constituting prohibited advertising under applicable texts (in particular for tobacco or alcohol);\n• constitutes sending unsolicited messages of a commercial nature;\n• intended to circumvent the social and tax rules applicable to job applications or offers;\n• incompatible with the protection of personal data;\n• constitutes denigration of a company or its products, parasitism, unfair competition or counterfeiting;\n• damaging the operation of the Site;\n• and more broadly infringing any law or regulation in force.\n6.3 Consequences of exclusion\nIn the event of exclusion of a Member, no liability of Mitiim may be incurred and all its job advertisements and/or service provider profiles will be deleted.\n6.4 Deletion of an account by a Member\nAny Member may, at any time, close their account, subject to compliance with the obligations imposed on them before this closure (provision of a service, payment of publication fees, Transaction between a Client and a Service Provider, etc.) .\n\n7. Basic contract\n7.1 Cost of registration\nThe registration request and registration are free for customers and chargeable for service providers except during promotional periods.\n7.2 Duration and termination\nThe contract for the use of basic functions (basic contract) of Mitiim is concluded for an indefinite period and may be terminated without notice by either party at any time. To terminate the contract, the User must delete the registration data on the “Personal information” tab of the “Account” menu by clicking on the “Delete my account” button. After that, the User receives a confirmation in the form of a banner directly on the Site.\n7.3 Consequence of termination\nThe User account will be deleted upon termination of the basic contract. After termination of the contract, the User cannot request the publication or restitution of the content he has published. Membership fees will not be refundable\n7.4 Access fees\nFees will be charged for providers, in order to have full access to the content and functions such as the publication of comments, the possibility of having access to the entire content of the site.',
