as Mitiim, which is only the host advertisements published on the Site by its Members, and is not notified, under the conditions provided for by law, of the content present on the Site presented as being illicit.\nThis being specified:\n• Mitiim invites Internet users and its Members to inform it, via the email address contact@Mitiim.com, of any possible abuse observed on the site;\n• Members who believe that the content inserted on the Site by an Internet user or another Member infringes their rights or the General Conditions can, if they wish, send a message to the address: contact@Mitiim.com.\n11.2 Contractual liability between a Client and a Service Provider when booking a service\nVERY IMPORTANT: WHEN MEMBERS AGREE IN COMPLETE FREEDOM, FROM THE ADS THAT THEY HAVE PUBLISHED ON THE SITE, ON THE PERFORMANCE OF A SERVICE PROVIDED, A CONTRACT IS FORMED BETWEEN THEM TO WHICH MITIIM IS NOT A PARTY. . THE CUSTOMER AND THE SERVICE PROVIDER ARE JOINT CONTRACTORS, INDEPENDENTLY OF MITIIM.\nNON-EXECUTION OR IMPROPER EXECUTION OF THIS CONTRACT BETWEEN MEMBERS IS NOT THE RESPONSIBILITY OF MITIIM BUT OF THAT OF THE Client OR THE SERVICE PROVIDER WHO HAS NOT RESPECTED THE OBLIGATIONS RESULTING FROM THE AGREEMENT WHICH HAS REACHED WITH THEIR CO-CONTRACTOR.\nFor this reason :\na) the Members of the Site declare to exonerate Mitiim from any liability:\n• relating to the responses or lack of response obtained following the publication of a job advertisement or a Service Provider Profile;\n• linked to the selection or non-selection of a Service Provider for a specific job advertisement;\n• relating to the smooth running or result of a service (for example the fact that a Service Provider does not show up, the quality of service, the service time, etc.);\n• relating to payment of a service;\n• linked to the control of the quality and progress of the service;\n• or more broadly in the event of conflict or litigation arising between Members.\nb) Members are solely responsible for direct or indirect, material or immaterial damage and harm caused to each other, to Mitiim and/or to any third party and undertake in particular to compensate Mitiim in the event of a request, claim and/or conviction to damages and interests of which Mitiim could be threatened or be the subject and/or which could be pronounced against the latter, including reasonable attorneys\' fees that Mitiim may have been required to incur, since these requests, claims and/or convictions would have the cause, basis or origin of information communicated by Members on the Site or the performance of services provided in application of information communicated by Members on the Site.',
