          '3. Personal data collected and processed when browsing the site\n3.1 Data collected and processed, purpose and method of collection\nMitiim may collect two types of personal data: mandatory data and optional data.\n3.1.1 Personal data collected compulsorily\nThe personal data required to be collected on the site are as follows:\n•\tFirst name\n•\tName\n•\tE-mail address\n•\tHome Address\n• Telephone number\n•\tIP adress\nFor Service Providers we also collect:\nIdentity documents or any other document necessary to prove eligibility for employment in the country of work and the chosen category of work\nThis data is collected when the user performs one of the following operations on the site:\n• When the Customer creates an account via the Mitiim form or via Facebook Login\n• When the Client creates a Job Advertisement\n• When the Client reserves a Service Provider\n• When the Customer uses a promotional code\nThis data is collected in order to:\n• Allow the Member to connect to their personal space\n• Allow the Site to communicate with the Member\n• Allow the Service Provider to know the location of his Service, and to contact his Client\n• Fight against fraud\n3.1.2 Personal data collected on an optional basis\nThe personal data collected on an optional basis for Customers on the site are as follows:\n•\tProfile picture\n•\tDate of birth\n•\tGender\n•\tMarital status\n• Tax allowances\nThis data is collected when the user performs one of the following operations on the site:\n• When the Customer completes their profile in full\n• When the Client mandates Mitiim to declare a Service Provider to the public administration\nThis data is collected in order to:\n• Allow the Member to build an attractive profile on the Site\n• Allow you to declare to the public administration the fact that a Client employs a Service Provider, if the Client has mandated Mitiim to do so.\n• Allow you to calculate and pay the social charges and tax reductions for which the Customer is eligible, if he or she has mandated the site to do so.\n\nIMPROVE YOUR MITIIM EXPERIENCE\n\nGEOLOCATION INFORMATION\nWhen you use the application via your mobile device, and only if you have consented to it, we track your geolocation information, in real time only. We use this information to allow you to see Customers/Service Providers in your area who are close to your location. Additionally, your choice to use certain features of the application during the journey, for example \"Share my journey\", will allow you to share your geolocation information with the people with whom you have chosen to share this information.\nIf you do not consent to the tracking of your geolocation, you will still be able to use the basic functionalities of the application. You can withdraw your consent at any time in your Mitiim account. Additionally, you can disable geolocation at the device level, even temporarily. Your mobile device notifies you when geolocation is being tracked by displaying the GPS arrow icon.\n\n\n3.1.3 Retention of personal data\nThe data controller will keep all the data collected in its site computer systems under reasonable security conditions for the following periods:\n• “cookies”, for a maximum duration of 13 months;\n• Data collected through prospecting, for a maximum of 3 years;\n• The data necessary for the tax declaration within the framework of which mandate is given to Mitiim, for 2 years;\n• The rest of the Data is kept for 3 years after the last use of the Platform if the Member has not deleted his account;\n• In the event of deletion of the Member\'s account, the Data is deleted within the legal deadlines depending on their type.\nThe collection and processing of data serves the following purposes:\n• Contact with a service provider,\n• “KYC” with our banking partners,\n• Affiliation with public administrations\n• Obligation of digital economy platforms\nThe data processing carried out is based on the following legal bases:\n• User consent\n• Explicit mandate given by the user during a reservation\nFurthermore, when paying on the site, proof of the transaction including the order form and invoice will be kept in the site publisher\'s computer systems.\n3.2 Transmission of data to third parties\nThe data may be transmitted to the third party(ies) listed below:\n• Data may be transferred to private or public law bodies if this is provided for by law\n• We may also disclose your information to authorities if we consider, in our sole discretion, that we are legally required or authorized to do so or that it would be prudent to do so.\nYour personal information cannot be transferred to and processed in another country.',
